@52   = ~Livery~
@53   = ~These garments appear to be a servant's livery. Keldorn recognizes the household as one in the Government district. He can take you to the estate, should you desire it.~
@54   = ~Ship Charters~
@55   = ~These documents appear to be receipts for the transport of several individuals to Memnon by sea. The dates span almost a decade, and all are signed by a person by the name of Vakola. The conditions on the charter state that the passenger will share a mess with the ship's officers, that the passenger must be granted privacy to study, and that the passenger will help defend the ship by arcane means in the event that the vessel is attacked.~
@56   = ~Zasheida's Journal~
@57   = ~For the most part, Zasheida's journal deals with the day-to-day frustrations of running a successful business while eluding Cowled Wizards. She expresses frequent exasperation that a person identified only as 'V' is becoming increasingly fanatical... and increasingly distant. She fears that their mutual enterprise may suffer because of V's growing aloofness.

On the last page of the journal, she complains that a recent surge in Athkatlan guard activity has necessitated the abandonment of a 'warehouse' in the Docks, but states that V has procured and outfitted a new location in the slums. She laments that conditions in the new location are deplorable, but that it must serve until the cargo can be transferred to the 'safe house' to await its departure for Memnon.

The location of the 'safe house' is not identified, but the journal contains clear and precise directions to the new storage area in the Slums. Anyone interested in finding it would merely have to go to the landmark specified, the dry-docked ship in the Slums, and follow the directions from there.~
@58   = ~Key to Zasheida's Room~
@59   = ~This ordinary-looking key has a number etched on it, which will make it easier to find Zasheida's room. The porter would appreciate the return of the key when you have finished with it.~
@60   = ~Zasheida's Talon~
@61   = ~The Scimitar is closely related to the saber, a single-edged curved sword with protective hilt.  A Scimitar has a greater curve and is tapered to an elongated, sharp point. The origins of the scimitar are largely unknown, though they have proven popular in the southern region of the Forgotten Realms.

STATISTICS:

